translated: Björkander, Carl-Johan, vicar, Katthammarsvik, b. June 10, 1888 in Hörsne, Gotland, son of Carl Julius B. and Augusta Hallberg. Married on June 16th to Thea Wallbom. Children: Carl-Johan b. 1917, Ingrid b. 1918, Per-Göran b. 1925. He passed Stud:-ex. in Uppsala in 1910, teol. fil. ex. in 1912, teol. kand., practical teol. ex. and was ordained as a priest in the archbishopric in 1915. Assistant vicar in Los, vicar in Östergarn, Ardre and Gammelgarn since 1920. Substitute member of the Church Assembly in 1932 and 1934, member in 1941 and 1946, member of the Visby Cathedral Chapter since 1943, of the ASP's central board since 1935, of the board of Östergarn's savings bank since 1934, chairman since 1928, chairman of the housing committee in Visby 'Diocese's first district since 1939, in the second since 1943, in Östergarn's municipality since 1928, in the municipal council since 1932. District forest ranger in Roma district from 1941 to 1945.
